                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/2286: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-18T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 18, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>976. Your 1017, April 17, noon. We are giving very careful study to the
                    suggestion you made and to the strong supporting arguments you advanced.</p>
                <p>If we have not come to a decision by the time you reach Washington,—and we hope
                    you will be starting on leave in the near future,—it will be extremely helpful
                    to discuss with you further the pros and cons of action along the lines you
                    suggest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
